Metasoma
. Petiole not entirely visible dorsally, very short, 0.12× as long as wide (
Figs 6C, D
), basal lamina absent dorsally, present ventrally, submedian carinae absent, lateral carinae absent; Gs1 projected forward under metasternum so petiole attached to Gt1 dorsum (
Fig. 6D
); dorsally, Gt1–Gt5 about 0.6× as wide as long (
Fig. 6C
); Gt6 with posterior margin slightly concave (
Fig. 6C
: red dashed line); Gt7+8 about 0.7× as long as Gt1–Gt6 combined (
Fig. 6D
).
